Former First Lady, Dame Patience Jonathan yesterday visited the First Lady, Aisha Buhari at the presidential Villa. On her Twitter handle , Aisha Buhari said they discussed her efforts in involving women in politics and governance. She also disclosed that they discussed the girl child education and her pet project “ women for change“. She tweeted “Yesterday, I received my predecessor, Her Excellency Dame Patience Jonathan at the State House. “We discussed my efforts with regards to greater involvement of women in politics & participation of women at lower level of governance. “We also discussed girl child education and her pet project “women for change. “I got to hear her experience during her tenure and listened to her perspectives on issues affecting women and children in the society. “It was really nice having her around and I look forward to having more of such moments,” she said.